Interface Set<Key_Type,Value_Type>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AVL_Tree, Binary_Tree, Hash_Map, List, Red_Black_Tree

    public interface Set<Key_Type,Value_Type>
    Interface which is used in the performance tests. Interface contains many basic data structure operations.

      • add_identical

        void add_identical(Key_Type key)
        Adds new node with given given key and value that is same as the key. Only works if key- and value types are the same. If key already exists in the set replaces old entry with new value.
        Parameters:
        key - Key that is added also determines value.

      • remove

        void remove(Key_Type key)
        Removes node with given key from the set. If key is not found from the set does nothing.
        Parameters:
        key - Key to be removed.
